def check(nums):
    count = 0
    for i in range(1, len(nums)):
        if nums[i] < nums[i - 1]:
            count += 1
        if count > 1:
            return False
    return count == 1 or nums[0] >= nums[-1]
```

    The algorithm iterates through the array and checks if the current element is less than the previous element. If it is, this creates a count variable incrementing by 1. If the count is greater than 1, it means there is more than one place where the array is not in non-decreasing order, so return false.

If the count is not greater than 1 after the iteration and is equal to 1 or the first element of the array is greater than or equal to the last element, it's a rotated non-decreasing array, so return true.

